guage":"Go","has_issues":true,"has_projects":true,"has_downloads":true,"has_wiki":false,"has_pages":false,"has_discussions":true,"forks_count":2054,"mirror_url":null,"archived":false,"disabled":false,"open_issues_count":823,"license":{"key":"apache-2.0","name":"Apache License 2.0","spdx_id":"Apache-2.0","url":"https://api.github.com/licenses/apache-2.0","node_id":"MDc6TGljZW5zZTI="},"allow_forking":true,"is_template":false,"web_commit_signoff_required":true,"topics":["cli","docker"],"visibility":"public","forks":2054,"open_issues":823,"watchers":5544,"default_branch":"master","permissions":{"admin":false,"maintain":false,"push":false,"triage":false,"pull":true}},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/docker/cli/pulls/3580","html_url":"https://github.com/docker/cli/pull/3580","diff_url":"https://github.com/docker/cli/pull/3580.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/docker/cli/pull/3580.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"<!--\r\nPlease make sure you've read and understood our contributing guidelines;\r\nhttps://github.com/docker/cli/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n\r\n** Make sure all your commits include a signature generated with `git commit -s` **\r\n\r\nFor additional information on our contributing process, read our contributing\r\nguide https://docs.docker.com/opensource/code/\r\n\r\nIf this is a bug fix, make sure your description includes \"fixes #xxxx\", or\r\n\"closes #xxxx\"\r\n\r\nPlease provide the following information:\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**- What I did**\r\nAdded `--all` to `docker kill`. This allows a user to easily send a signal to all running containers. \r\n\r\n**- How I did it**\r\nI had made a new func `RequiresArgOrAllFlag` which makes sure a cmd has either args passed to it or has the `--all` flag set. This will be especially useful should `stop` and `rm` get an `--all` flag. Other than that I used the functionality of `ps` to get the containers using the `status=running` filter.\r\n\r\n**- How to verify it**\r\nI added new unit test file to cover the `kill --all` functionality as well as the already existing `kill` functionality.\r\n\r\nfunctionality looks like this:\r\n```bash\r\n$ for i in $(seq 3); do docker run -itd alpine sh; done;\r\nb776410ee32895527d804ec7ee08ca7d3ef20c9a4fefc1ebe1384cbfdf8bd051\r\n56245ce81708d8d3eae8c7bc920f353deb2bb6b62d2fa8668b3ebc8ba2c6581e\r\nbd8a998578173134eed2266d51572f861bea3f33aa79b2292a967052329c8b7e\r\n$ docker kill --all\r\nb776410ee32895527d804ec7ee08ca7d3ef20c9a4fefc1ebe1384cbfdf8bd051\r\n56245ce81708d8d3eae8c7bc920f353deb2bb6b62d2fa8668b3ebc8ba2c6581e\r\nbd8a998578173134eed2266d51572f861bea3f33aa79b2292a967052329c8b7e\r\n$ docker kill --all -s SIGINT\r\nno containers running to send SIGINT signal to\r\n$ docker kill --all some-container\r\n\"docker kill\" requires at least 1 argument or --all flag.\r\nSee 'docker kill --help'.\r\n\r\nUsage:  docker kill [OPTIONS] CONTAINER [CONTAINER...]\r\n\r\nKill one or more running containers\r\n```\r\n\r\n**- Description for the changelog**\r\n<!--\r\nWrite a short (one line) summary that describes the changes in this\r\npull request for inclusion in the changelog:\r\n-->\r\nIntroduce  `kill --all` to send a signal to all running containers\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/docker/cli/issues/3565\r\n\r\n***Additional Information***\r\nI decided not to make a `rm --all` like the issue conversation suggests because I think there might be a functionality conflict. `docker container prune` requires either a confirmation or a `--force` flag. I think that making `docker rm --all` remove all containers without confirmation could lead to an unpredictable experience for the end user. I'd be open to suggestions, but I'm not sure if it is necessary given `docker prune` exists. Maybe I'm missing something; I would be happy to hear your thoughts about this and about `docker stop --all` :smiley: \r\n\r\n\r\n**- A picture of a cute animal (not mandatory but encouraged)**\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/73488828/16613